<br>
We aimed at doing raids on the second teir spots on Norrath. Before Kunark (and the lvl 52 rule) we never did a dragon in a guild raid. We couldn't... Da'Kor/Ice and/or MS would kill them within a hour of servers coming up, we just couldn't compete with them as our players were still at work, looking after family, picking the kids up from school etc. Where we concentrated was in spots like Kedge Keep and The Hole, and I challange any guild to say they can do those zones better than Affliction. <br>
<br>
Affliction has always been a &quot;lets look for a challange but lets make sure we have fun&quot; guild rather than the &quot;lets stay up 36 hours strait till we kill that god and the first person who logs gets booted&quot; guild. <br>
<br>
I have to agree with Nocrad about missing the challange by jumping to a end-game guild like Da'Kor. Think about it like this, being with Da'Kor on a raid is like playing Quake in god mode. Maybe thats how you play Quake and you think your a awesome player, but your not realy. <br>
<br>
Sure you'll have the best toys on the server, but did you have fun? Maybe, they are a great group of people but the biggest challange you went through in the game was getting into the guild. <br>
