<br>
And as far as the whole &quot;Affliction/Da'Kor recruiting&quot; thing I have no comment except the following :<br>
<br>
People switch guilds for pretty much the same reason they switch jobs. Better conditions, more money, more action.<br>
<br>
If you honestly believe people join guilds like Affliction or Da'Kor for companionship, you are seriously deluded. People join to get in on the ownage. Whether or not they grow to feel some sort of kinship is irrelevant, the initial drive to get into one of these exclusive circles is because they are where the action is.<br>
<br>
Sort of like when you land that cushy job and make friends with the guy in the next cubicle. The friendship is incidental, but the whole reason you are both there is the action.<br>
<br>
So don't get mad when that same guy in the next cubicle suddenly gets a better offer and starts packing because it's nothing personal. When your guild treats itself like a business, others treat it like a business too. Nothing personal, I can get more stuff with Da'Kor.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile there are still people in this game who are level 10, wearing patchwork, in a Roleplaying guild nobody has heard of with 5 close friends, and they wouldn't change guilds if you offered them all the treasure in KC.<br>
<br>
Just a thought.<br>
